  group_by(dat, team),
  median_points3 = mean(points3)
)

First contact with ggplot()

scatterplot of height and weight
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(data = gsw) + geom_point(aes(x = gsw$height, y = gsw$weight))

scatterplot of height and weight with player names
ggplot(data = gsw) + geom_point(aes(x = gsw$height, y = gsw$weight)) + geom_text(x = gsw$height, y = gsw$weight, label = gsw$player)

ggplot(data = gsw) + geom_point(aes(x = gsw$height, y = gsw$weight)) + geom_label(x = gsw$height, y = gsw$weight, label = gsw$player)

density plot of salary for all NBA players
ggplot(data = dat) + geom_density(aes(dat$salary))

histogram of points 2
ggplot(data = dat) + geom_histogram(aes(dat$points2), bins = 50)

barchart of position
library(ggplot2)
ggplot(data = dat) + geom_bar(aes(dat$position))

scatterplot of experience and salary with regression line
dfc <- data.frame(dat$position == 'C')
ggplot(data = dfc) + geom_point(aes(x = dat$experience, y = dat$salary)) + geom_smooth(method = lm, formula = y ~ x, aes(x = dat$experience, y = dat$salary))

scatterplot of experience and salary with loess line
# scatterplot of experience and salary with loess line

dfc <- data.frame(dat$position == 'C')
ggplot(data = dfc) + geom_point(aes(x = dat$experience, y = dat$salary)) + geom_smooth(aes(x = dat$experience, y = dat$salary))
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Faceting

ggplot(data = dat, aes(x = experience, y = salary)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ position)

ggplot(data = dat, aes(x = experience, y = salary)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ team)

ggplot(data = dat, aes(age)) +
  geom_density() +
  facet_wrap(~ team)

ggplot(data = dat, aes(x = height, y = weight)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_wrap(~ position)

ggplot(data = dat, aes(x = height, y = weight)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_density2d() +
  facet_wrap(~ position)

ggplot(data = gsw, aes(x = experience, y = salary)) +
  geom_point() +
  theme_bw()

ggplot(data = dat, aes(age)) +
  geom_density() +
  theme_dark()+
  facet_wrap(~ team)
